{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nR1 changes what pass 1 finds on EVERY review; the epic's gate requires <=2% PASS->BLOCK flips on cleanly-closed tickets. Only a counterfactual replay of the amended gate over real historical reviews can measure verdict churn before production exposure.\n\n## What\nRe-run the amended gate (each R-candidate as packaged registry/rubric edits on an experiment branch build - no overlay/config-flag mechanism, per operator direction) over a stratified ~200-review historical sample via the production_batch_runner seam; compute the verdict-transition matrix (PASS->PASS/PASS->BLOCK/BLOCK->PASS/BLOCK->BLOCK), segmented by IMPACT_MODEL_VERSION per ADR 0036 (never pooled across versions). Stratification: ticket type, overlay triggers, verdict, model. Record per-criterion finding deltas alongside verdict flips so an R-row's churn is attributable.\n\n## Scope\n- docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/ (replay driver extending production_batch_runner usage + runs/ output + writeup).\n- Live LLM calls (billable): the replay runs the real pipeline; sample size ~200 bounded.\n- NO packaged gate changes land from this story; candidate edits live on the experiment branch only.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The stratified ~200-review sample is committed (ids + strata) before the replay runs, drawn from the E1 outcome corpus.\n- [ ] The replay executes the candidate branch build over the full sample and commits the verdict-transition matrix segmented by IMPACT_MODEL_VERSION, with per-criterion finding deltas.\n- [ ] The PASS->BLOCK flip rate on cleanly-closed tickets is computed and recorded per candidate (the input consumed by R1's <=2% gate row).\n- [ ] A docs/experiments/ writeup documents method, cost, and per-candidate results."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784143734462154001,"uuid":"afba9bff-2c11-48f8-a8aa-4c33ebcb3c00"}